Swisscom to Invest 1.5 Billion Euros in Italy, CEO Tells Il Sole

-- B y   A l e s s a n d r a   M i g l i a c c i o
-- 
2011-10-01T13:43:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-01/swisscom-to-invest-1-5-billion-euros-in-italy-ceo-tells-il-sole.html
     Oct. 1 (Bloomberg) -- Swisscom AG (SCMN)  plans to invest 1.5
billion euros ($2 billion) in Italy in the next five years,
Chief Executive Officer Carsten Schloter told daily  Il Sole 24
Ore  in an interview.  Swisscom, which owns Italian telecommunications company
Fastweb SpA, said the money will be invested in next-generation
networks, according to Il Sole.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alessandra Migliaccio in Rome at 
 amigliaccio@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Kennedy at 
 wkennedy3@bloomberg.net  